**Response:**

Ниже приведён план разработки хранилища данных для CLI‑трекера личных расходов, который полностью удовлетворяет ограничениям (только stdlib, JSON‑файлы, без сторонних пакетов).

**Draft Plan:**
```json
[
  {
    "title": "Define data model",
    "description": "Specify the fields for each expense record (e.g., id, date, amount, category, comment, tags). Use dataclasses for type safety and easy conversion to/from dict."
  },
  {
    "title": "Design JSON file structure",
    "description": "Create a single JSON file (e.g., expenses.json) that stores a list of expense objects. Include a top‑level metadata section for next_id and optional indexes."
  },
  {
    "title": "Implement CRUD operations",
    "description": "Write functions to create, read, update, and delete records: load the JSON file into memory, modify the list, then write it back. Ensure atomic writes by using a temporary file and os.replace."
  },
  {
    "title": "Add simple indexing for fast queries",
    "description": "Maintain in‑memory dictionaries (e.g., by_date, by_category) after loading the file. Rebuild indexes on each write; this keeps query performance acceptable for a few thousand records."
  },
  {
    "title": "Provide backup and history",
    "description": "On each write, copy the existing JSON file to a backup folder with a timestamped filename. Optionally keep a limited number of backups to avoid disk bloat."
  },
  {
    "title": "Integrate with CLI interface",
    "description": "Expose the CRUD functions via command‑line commands (add, list, edit, delete, export). Use argparse for argument parsing and format output as plain text or a simple table."
  }
]
```

Пожалуйста, подтвердите, подходит ли вам такой план, или укажите, какие пункты нужно изменить/добавить.
